caption: Great experience! The personnel was very nice and helpful.

This was my first visit every to any type of park like this one and i am from Canada. They have 12 different levels. They gave very detailed explanations to have as much fun. I do suggest you go with long pants rather than shorts to prevent scruffs and probably gloves. It makes holding the ropes much more comfortable. Although it was a hot day, i did not feel the heat much as there were plenty of trees around. The staff were very courteous/ Nice and helpful. I do find there should be a bit more staff within the parkour for safety purposes. I plan on going back next time i go back to Paris to face my fears.
Love going there with my family! Kids friendly , my baby is 2 and she has a blast there evrytime. It's also  very challenging for adults ,and the staff is nice!

Great Park !!!The park is excellent with facilities suitable for all ages. Even the big ones have a great challenge and it is very difficult in the 7th and 8th stages. The prices are more than fair and the staff are really charming !!! Recommended for the whole family and for those looking for the challenge.
Can be scary at times, even medium-hard routes. Staff is very friendly and routes are superb. Toilets need an upgrade.
12 lines. Plenty infrastructures for various choice of levels. Line no.10~12 is for ones who expects a challenge.
The scenery is beautiful and very fresh. You should come here to experience it every time
Absolutely incredible and terrifying, said as two adults. Staff were basically superhero squirrels.
Adventurous.. great time with kids
Good adventure.., staff excellent

Superb park that I visited yesterday. Lots of courses, all different from each other, very diverse. Thank you again for this experience, a great place to come with family, with a group of children, and the operators are very friendly and attentive.  The only negative point is the toilets, we will have to think about completely redoing them because they are dirty and full of insects.

Dissatisfied it is marked that the park closes at 7:30 p.m. and 6:15 p.m. see before all the courses are closed. We can't even start a higher level even if it means going down through an escape route. The price is excessive for a treetop adventure The platforms at the top of the trees are poorly fixed... In short, I don't recommend it

Superbly well redeveloped park (the last time I came was at least 5 years ago!). The levels of the courses are progressive, special mention at the start of the red which is VERY difficult (but satisfying to accomplish). I came for the first time, 30 minutes later it was raining heavily, emergency evacuation, they agreed to give us a credit üëåüëå

The courses are great, with minimalist platforms on the trees which accentuate the sensations of height. üëç On the other hand, I found my harness not very comfortable on the zip lines. I've been to this place several times and honestly I'm never disappointed. The courses are really good and varied (unlike other parks of this type), the explanations are clear and the equipment is safe, not forgetting the staff who are always really friendly and available if needed. The only downside is the toilets are not very clean but hey not the most important. Otherwise we really have a good time there, happy to have it close to home.

Very friendly welcome, super pleasant park suitable for everyone, the courses are really great. Our 4 and a half year old child did 4 courses, he loved it. We will come back with pleasure! Many thanks.

No sense of business the park is supposed to close at 7:00 p.m. they force you to start with easy or family courses and then at 6:00 p.m. prohibit you from doing higher levels under the pretext that the park must be closed, incredible 28 euros to make us leave 1h30 before the scandalous closure

Superb place for tree climbing and zip lining. There is also the trampoline and nets. Several courses depending on the level, ideal for family or friends. Birthdays can also be celebrated. Top team and available. I recommend

I visited the park in August with two children under 6 years old. Very warm welcome. Small, pleasant area for children, and away from the other courses, which is very pleasant, and makes it easier to keep an eye on the children while letting them have fun on their own.  We will come back to try the adult courses!

Great experience, we were 2 adults and 2 children we had time to do 4 courses with varying levels of difficulty. The whole team is adorable and caring. The courses are very suitable for all levels, from beginners to advanced. We can't wait to go back as adults to do the most difficult ones. thanks to the whole team
Very nice place, it's perfect for little ones. The staff is very nice. And I loved the dry toilets. The course consists of three parts. Prices are correct.

Honestly great there, the guides are really great, they explain well beforehand and are very friendly and kind. The attractions are great and there are even small courses made for children. And for those who like thrills there are also some. In the top!

An experience that could have been much nicer. In fact, it is impossible to start a new course more than an hour before closing, knowing that it requires us to do courses beforehand in order to ‚Äòjustify the level‚Äô. Not at all commercial especially considering the price. Bad toilets, some boards are shaky

It was our first time at the treetop adventure course. we had a great afternoon there. everything was well organized! the harnesses were waiting for us. the explanations before the courses were very clear. the staff is friendly, always ready to answer or help us. there are courses for all levels, from toddlers to adventurers! the setting is really nice. we will happily return!
Very beautiful park and trails suitable for all ages. Very clear explanations, friendly and professional welcome. only downside, the toilets which really need to be improved.

Beautiful picnic area. We did the course for little ones (3 years old). He had a great time. Zipline and other routes are easily accessible.

Wow! It was so good! Full of emotions! Warm welcome, adorable person, calm, smiling, takes the time to explain. It was our first time and thanks to Agathe and Nicolas it was perfect!!!! Thank you very much!!!!!!
Very pretty park. I had a pleasant time with my daughter, my little princess. Very varied routes for everyone Fun guaranteed after mastering the security system. I highly recommend ;)
